definition.value: Methylmalonic aciduria is a genetically heterogeneous disorder of methylmalonate and cobalamin (cbl; vitamin B12) metabolism.

Proerythroblasts are the earliest recognizable erythroid precursors. They are followined during the process of hematopoiesis by basophilic erythroblasts, polychromatic (polychromatophilic) erythroblasts, orthochromatic erythroblasts (normoblasts), reticulocytes, and finally mature erythrocytes (red blood cells). This term encompasses structural anomalies of erythroblast precursors in the bone marrow.
Any structural anomaly of megakaryocytes. Mature blood platelets are released from the cytoplasm of megakaryocytes, which are bone-marrow resident cells.
Any structural anomaly of a myeloid mononuclear recirculating leukocyte that can act as a precursor of tissue macrophages, osteoclasts and some populations of tissue dendritic cells.

label.value: Abnormality of multiple cell lineages in the bone marrow

definition.value: The major apolipoproteins of HDL are apolipoprotein (apo) A-I and apo A-II, also known as the alpha lipoproteins. Thus, hyperalphalipoproteinemia refers to an elevated concentration of apo A-I and apo A-II.

Increased porphobilinogen (PBG) in urine is pathognomonic of an attack of acute porphyria (acute intermittent porphyria, variegate porphyria, hereditary coproporphyria); the absence of increased urinary PBG in a suspected attack excludes the diagnosis.
Agranulocytosis is defined as an absolute neutrophil count less than 500 cells/microliter.
Sweat chloride is notably increased in cystic fibrosis, but also in some other diseases.
